text: Sumichrast's tree frog (Exerodonta sumichrasti) is a frog that lives in Mexico. Scientists have seen it in cloud forests between 200 and 2000 meters above sea level on the Pacific Ocean side (west side) of the mountains. It lives in the states of Guerrero, Oaxaca, and Chiapas. ==References== Category:Frogs of North America
title: Exerodonta sumichrasti
